    "Id": "chassisdef_rook_NH-2",
    "Name": "Rook",
    "Details": "The NH-2 Rook upgrades almost every component of the original. The chassis, armor, and engine are all modern but affordable, as are the electronics. Two heat sinks were removed but the remaining twelve are upgraded to double heat sinks. The original PPC is upgraded to an ER PPC. The head-mounted small laser, the design's anti-infantry component, is now a Small Pulse Laser, far more effective at its task. The two rear-facing medium lasers were removed and the four remaining are more modern models. If the Rook NH-2 shines in any regard it is the Improved Jump Jets that allow it to jump over obstacles at the same speed as it can cover flat ground.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Rugged</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.05</color></b>",
